    "biography": "<p>Wild animals that live in large, grazing herds. The exact type depends on the terrain.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Stampede:&nbsp;</strong>Herds of 20 or more can trample those in their path. 3-in-4 chance each round. +4 to hit human-sized or smaller creatures. 1d20 damage.</li>\n<li><strong>Males:</strong>&nbsp;In groups of 3 or more, only 1-in-4 are males. These have 1d4 extra hit points and protect the herd.</li>\n<li><strong>Females and young:</strong>&nbsp;Flee from danger. Females do not have a butt attack. Young have half normal hit points.</li>\n</ul>"
